Acidic Splatter					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																																														DESC:As long as you have an acid spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can throw an orb of acid as a ranged touch attack. The attack has a range of 5 feet per level of the highest-level acid spell you have available to cast and deals 1d6 points of damage per level of that acid spell. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting acid spells.																										BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SUBSCHOOL.Acid|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.37
Alacritous Cogitation				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																																																	PRESPELLCAST:TYPE=Arcane	PRESPELLCAST:MEMORIZE=Y																												DESC:You can leave a prepares spell slot open to spontaneously cast a spell.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.37																			BENEFIT:If you leave an arcane spell slot open when preparing spells, you can use that open slot to cast any spell you know of the same level or lower. Casting the spell will be extended to a full round action (provided the spell is normally a standard action).
Aquatic Breath					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:Your reservoir of magic allows you to breathe normally even underwater.																																																																																BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Water|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.39																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a water spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can breathe normally in both air and water. This supernatural quality requires no activation. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting water spells.
Battlecaster Defense				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=1					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Casting																																																																									DESC:You have mastered techniques for taking full advantage of spells in melee combat while remaining unharmed.																																																			MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.39																			BENEFIT:Gain 3 maneuvers.  Defensive Targeting - Cast a spell with a range of touch using the defensive casting option. If you succeed in delivering the spell, you gain a +2 to all touch attacks against that target next round.  Practiced Defense - When you successfully use defensive casting 2 consecutive rounds, You gain a +10 to your Concentration check in the 3rd round.  Safe Retreat - When you succeed in a defensive casting, your movement on the next turn won't provoke Attacks of Opportunity from the creatures that threatened you during the casting.																																																																																					PRETOTALAB:1
Battlecaster Offensive				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Casting],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Warmage Edge]					PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=4																																									DESC:You cunningly mix melee combat and spellcasting to increase the potency of both.																																																							MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:Gain 2 maneuvers.  Spell and Sword - If you deal damage to a foe with a spell, you gain a +1 bonus on your first melee attack roll made against him next round.  Sword and Spell - If you make a melee attack against a foe, you gain a +1 to the DC of a spell cast against him in the next round.																																																																																																																																	PRETOTALAB:1
Blade of Force					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You can surround a weapon with a short-lived aura of force.																																																																																		BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Force|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a 3rd-level or higher force spell available to cast, you can surround a melee weapon or a single piece of ammunition with a thin field of force. Activating this ability is a swift action; you must touch the weapon to be affected as part of the action. The next attack made with that weapon, if taken before the end of your next turn, deals an extra 1 point of damage per level of the highest-level force spell you have available to cast. Furthermore, that weapon ignores the miss chance normally granted to an incorporeal creature. If the next attack with that weapon misses, this benefit is lost. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting force spells.
Borne Aloft						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=5,SPELLCASTER.Divine=5																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 5th-level spells.																		DESC:You can channel the magic of the winds to briefly grant you flight.																																																																																BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Air|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an air spell of 5th level or higher available to cast, you can fly up to 30 feet (perfect maneuverability) as a move action once per round. You must begin and end this flight solidly supported, or you fall. You can't use this ability if you wear heavy armor or carry a heavy load. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting air spells.
Captivating Melody				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Bardic Music																																																							PRESPELLCAST:TYPE=Arcane																																DESC:You can expend some of your musical abilities to increase the potency of your enchantment or illusion spells.																																																		MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:As a swift action, attempt a Perform check (DC 15 + the spell level) to sacrifice a use of bardic music to increase the save DC of your next enchantment or illusion spell by 2. You loose the music use whether you succeed or fail the check. You can only apply this to spells granted by the class granting the music ability.
Clap of Thunder					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You can deliver a thunderous roar with a touch.																																																																																				BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Sonic|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a sonic spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can deliver a melee touch attack as a standard action. This attack deals ld6 points of sonic damage per level of the highest-level sonic spell you have available to cast. Additionally, the subject must succeed on a Fortitude save or be deafened for 1 round. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting sonic spells.
Cloud Conjuration					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Conjuration)],[PRECLASS:1,Conjurer=1]																																																					DESC:Your conjured creations and summoned beings appear in a puff of sickening black smoke, and you vanish in a cloud of the same when you teleport.																																													MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:When you cast a conjuration spell, you can choose to have a 5-ft.-radius cloud of sickening smoke manifest. The cloud can appear in your square, your target square, or any square adjacent to either. The cloud lasts for 1 round. Any living creature in the smoke is sickened while inside the cloud (no save) unless they are immune to poison. Your summoned or called creatures are automatically immune to the cloud's effects.
Clutch of Earth					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 2nd-level spells.																		DESC:You briefly increase the earth's pull on the target creature.																																																																																	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Earth|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.40																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an earth spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can spend a standard action to reduce the speed of any landbound creature within 30 feet of you. The creature's normal land speed, as well as its burrow and climb speeds, decrease by 5 feet per level of the highestlevel earth spell you have available to cast, to a minimum speed of 5 feet. This effect lasts for 1 round. A successful Fortitude save negates this effect and renders the target immune to the feat's effect for 24 hours. Creatures currently swimming or flying are immune to this effect. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting earth spells.
Dazzling Illusion					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Illusion)],[PRECLASS:1,Illusionist=1]																																																					DESC:Casting illusions cause the air about you to be filled with flashing colors that dazzle your foes.																																																				MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.41																			BENEFIT:When you cast an illusion spell, you can choose to render all enemies within 30 feet dazzled for 1 round. Blind creatures are immune to this effect.
Defending Spirit					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard	PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Watchful Spirit																																																																																											DESC:Your watchful spirit helps keep you safe in combat.																																																												MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.41																			BENEFIT:Your watchful spirit helps you defend yourself. If you use an initiative reroll from your watchful spirit class feature, you gain a +2 dodge bonus to AC for the duration of the encounter.  This adds 1 use of Watchful spirit for for each day.
Delay Potion					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																																										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Arcana)=1																																							DESC:You can drink a potion and postpone its effects.																																																													MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.41																			BENEFIT:You can drink a potion and delay its effects for a number of hours equal to your Constitution modifier. At any time during this period you may activate the potion's effects as a swift action.  If the duration expires before you activate the potion, the potion is wasted. You may delay only one potion at a time.
Dimensional Jaunt					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=4,SPELLCASTER.Divine=4																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 4th-level spells.																		DESC:With a single step, you can cross an entire room.																																																																																			BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Force|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.41																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a teleportation spell of 4th level or higher available to cast, you can spend a standard action to teleport yourself and carried objects up to your heavy load a distance of 5 feet per level of the highest-level teleportation spell you have available to cast. You can teleport only to a location that you can see (including one you are currently scrying). You can't bring along another creature (except for a familiar). As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting teleportation spells.
Dimensional Reach					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You can transport small objects to you with an act of will.																																																																																		BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SUBSCHOOL.Summoning|1|TYPE=Competence																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.41																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a conjuration (summoning) spell of 3rd level higher available to cast, you can transport small items directly into your hand as a standard action. You must have line of sight to an item you wish to transport in this way, and it must be unattended. This ability works at a range of up to 5 feet per level of the highest-level summoning spell you have available to cast, and the item can weigh up to 2 pounds per level of that spell. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting conjuration (summoning) spells.
Drowning Glance					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=4,SPELLCASTER.Divine=4																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 4th-level spells.																		DESC:With a look, you create a small but incapacitating amount of water in the subject's lungs.																																																																													BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Water|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.41																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a water spell of 4th level or higher available to cast, you can use a standard action to transform a small portion of the air in a living creature's lungs to water, making it difficult for the creature to breathe. The subject must be within 30 feet. The target becomes exhausted for 1 round; if it succeeds on a Fortitude save, it is instead fatigued for 1 round. Whether or not a targeted creature successfully saves, it is immune to any further uses of your drowning glance for 24 hours. Creatures that can breathe water (or who don't breathe) are immune to this effect. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting water spells.
Elemental Adept					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Elemental Mastery																																																																																											DESC:You can spontaneously cast a spell of the element you have mastered.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.42																			BENEFIT:Choose one spell from your mastered element. You may spontaneously cast it using any spell slot of equal or higher level. Every time you gain a level, you may change the specified spell.
Energy Abjuration					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Abjuration)],[PRECLASS:1,Abjurer=1]																																																					DESC:Casting an abjuration spell grants you protection from energy damage.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.42																			BENEFIT:When you cast an abjuration spell, you can choose to gain a special energy resistance equal to (1 + the spell's level) x 5. This lasts for the duration of the spell you cast or until you are struck by any type of energy damage. The resistance applies only for the first energy damage you take.
Energy Gestalt					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER=3					PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Evocation)																																																																								DESC:You have learned to combine multiple energy effects to great advantage.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.42																			BENEFIT:You gain 3 maneuvers. Acrid Fumes - You cast an acid spell followed by a fire spell. The flames turn the lingering acid into choking, sickening fumes. Any living creature damaged by both spells is nauseated for a round (or sickened if they make a Fortitude save DC from fire spell). Treat this as a poison effect for immunities/resitances.  Brittle Blast - You cast a cold spell followed by a sonic spell. Any object or construct damaged by both spells takes +50%% damage from the sonic spell.  Improved Conduction - Cast a cold spell followed by an electricity spell. Thie lingering cold improves conduction. Foes damaged by both spells are slowed for 1 round (per the spell) or fatigued for 1 round if they make a Fortitude save DC based on the 2nd spell.
Face-Changer					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:Your mastery of illusions allows you to subtly alter your appearance at whim.																																																																															BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SUBSCHOOL.Glamer|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.42																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a glamer spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can alter your appearance as the spell disguise self, except that the duration lasts 1 minute per level of the glamer spell. This illusory transformation requires a full-round action to activate. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting glamer spells.
Favored Magic Foe (Aberration)		CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																						PREMULT:1,[PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Dungeoneering)=6],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Favored Enemy ~ Aberration]																																													DESC:Through study, you have learned how best to defend yourself against your favored enemies' spells and how to best affect them with your own.																																													MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.42																			BENEFIT:You gain a +1 to overcome spell resistance rolls for your favored enemy and such creatures take a -1 penalty on saves against your spells and spell-like abilities.
