Fearsome Necromancy				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Necromancy)],[PRECLASS:1,Necromancer=1]																																																				DESC:Creatures subject to your necromancy spells fear the chill of fear.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.42																			BENEFIT:Any foe required to save against a necromancy spell you cast is shaken for 1 round, regardless of the save result. The mind-affecting fear ability does not stack with this effect.
Fey Heritage					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fey												!PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE																																																																																							DESC:YYou are descended from creatures native to the fey realms. You are naturally resistant to the most common effects produced by your ancestors.																																													MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.43	ASPECT:SAVEBONUS|+3 on Will saves vs. enchantment effects									BENEFIT:You gain a +3 bonus on Will saves against enchantment spells and effects.
Fey Legacy						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fey												!PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fey Heritage							PRELEVEL:MIN=9																																																SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Confusion,14+CHA|Dimension Door|Summon Nature's Ally V		DESC:The magical powers of your ancestors manifest in you.																																																												MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:You gain the following spell-like abilities, each usable once per day: confusion, dimension door, and summon nature's ally V. Your caster level equals your character level.
Fey Power						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fey												!PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fey Heritage																																																																										DESC:Your fey heritage augments the power of certain types of magic.																																																										MULT:NO																						BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL=Enchantment|1															BONUS:DC|SCHOOL=Enchantment|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:Your caster level and save DCs for enchantment spells and warlock invocations is increased by 1.
Fey Presence					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fey												!PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fey Heritage							PRELEVEL:MIN=6																																																SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Charm Monster,14+CHA|Deep Slumber,13+CHA|Disguise Self,11+CHA	DESC:You share your ancestors' knack for playing tricks on the minds of others.																																																								MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:You gain the following spell-like abilities, each usable once per day: charm monster, deep slumber, and disguise self. Your caster level equals your character level.
Fey Skin						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fey												!PREALIGN:LG,LN,LE										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fey Heritage																																																																										DESC:Your fey heritage guards you against all weapons except those crafted from the dreaded cold iron.																																																				MULT:NO																																																BONUS:DR|cold iron|(1+COUNT[FEATTYPE=Fey])															SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:You gain damage reduction (cold iron) equal to 1 + the number of Fey Heritage feats that you have. This value stacks with other DR you may have.
Fiendish Heritage					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fiendish											!PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG																																																																																							DESC:You are descended from creatures native to the lower planes. You share some of your ancestors' natural resistance to poison and you are resistant to the the magic of good foes. MULT:NO																																																																																																													SOURCEPAGE:p.43	ASPECT:SAVEBONUS|+4 on Fortitude saves vs. poison, +1 on saves vs. spells and effects cast by good casters.	BENEFIT:You gain a +4 bonus on Fortitude saving throws against poison. You also gain a +1 bonus on saving throws against spells or other effects produced by good creatures.
Fiendish Legacy					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fiendish											!PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fiendish Heritage						PRELEVEL:MIN=9																																																SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Summon Monster V|Teleport|Unholy Blight,14+CHA				DESC:The magical powers of your ancestors manifest in you.																																																												MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:You gain the following spell-like abilities, each usable once per day: teleport (self plus 50 pounds of objects only), summon monster V (fiendish creatures only), and unholy blight. You caster level equals your character level.
Fiendish Power					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fiendish											!PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fiendish Heritage																																																																									DESC:Your fiendish heritage augments the power of certain types of magic.																																																									MULT:NO																						BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR=Evil|1																BONUS:DC|DESCRIPTOR=Evil|1																							SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:Your caster level and save DCs for evil spells and warlock invocations is increased by 1.
Fiendish Presence					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fiendish											!PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fiendish Heritage						PRELEVEL:MIN=6																																																SPELLS:Innate|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=TL|Cause Fear,11+CHA|Detect Thoughts,12+CHA|Suggestion,13+CHA		DESC:You share your ancestors' ability to tamper with the minds of weak-minded fools.																																																							MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:You gain the following spell-like abilities, each usable once per day: cause fear, detect thoughts, and suggestion. Your caster level equals your character level.
Fiendish Resistance				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Fiendish											!PREALIGN:LG,NG,CG										PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Fiendish Heritage																																																																									DESC:Your bloodline inures you against corrosion and fire.																																																												MULT:NO							ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Resistance to Acid|Resistance to Fire																																						BONUS:VAR|AcidResistanceBonus,FireResistanceBonus|(COUNT[FEATTYPE=Fiendish]*3)	SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:You gain resistance to acid and fire equal to three times the number of fiendish feats you have. These values stack with any existing resistances.
Fiery Burst						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 2nd-level spells.																		DESC:You channel your magical talent into a blast of fire.																																																																																			BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Fire|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.43																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a fire spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can spend a standard action to create a 5-foot-radius burst of fire at a range of 30 feet. This burst deals ld6 points of fire damage per level of the highestlevel fire spell you have available to cast. A successful Reflex save halves the damage. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting fire spells.
Hasty Spirit					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Watchful Spirit																																																																																											DESC:Your watchful spirit lends you a burst of speed in times of great need.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:In an encounter you use your watchful spirit feature, you may make 1 additional move action on one of your turns.  This feat also adds an extra use of the watchful spirit feature.
Hurricane Breath					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 2nd-level spells.																		DESC:The power of elemental air you hold in your mind allows you to exhale the wind.																																																																														BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Air|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an air spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can attempt to knock a single creature within 30 feet back with a blast of wind. This requires a standard action and functions much like a bull rush; roll 1d20 + the level of the highest-level air spell you have available to cast opposed by your opponent's Strength check. If you succeed, you push the creature back 5 feet. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting air spells.
Insightful Divination				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Divination)],[PRECLASS:1,Diviner=1]																																																					DESC:Casting a divination spell grants you an uncanny insight into danger.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:When you cast a divination spell, you gain an insight bonus equal to 1 + the spell level on initiative checks and the first saving throw you make for the next 24 hours. If cast a 2nd divination spell you may choose to replace the bonus with the level of the new spell, they do not stack.
Invisible Needle					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You can create tiny darts of force.																																																																																						BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Force|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a force spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can use a standard action to hurl a tiny needle-shaped projectile created from pure force. This attack requires a successful ranged attack roll (not a ranged touch attack), and the dart has a range of 5 feet per level of the force spell. The needle deals ld4 points of damage per level of the highest-level force spell you have available. Because it is composed of force, the needle can strike incorporeal creatures. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting force spells.
Magic Device Attunement				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																																										PRESKILL:1,Use Magic Device=1																																								DESC:You have a knack for activating familiar magic items.																																																												MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:If you successfully activate a magic item with a Use Magic Device check, you can take a free action to attune to it. For the next 24 hours, you can activate it without a new skill check. You can be attuned to only 1 device at a time.
Magic Disruption					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You can use your powers of abjuration to interfere with other casters' spells.																																																																															BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL.Abjuration|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an abjuration spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can attempt to interrupt another character's spellcasting with a tiny burst of magic. As an immediate action, you can force any character within 30 feet currently casting a spell to make a Concentration check (DC 15 + the level of the highest-level abjuration spell you have available to cast); if the check fails, the spell's save DC and caster level are reduced by 2 (to a minimum caster level of 1st). As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting abjuration spells.
Magic Sensitive					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You literally see the emanations of magic around you.																																																																																			BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL.Divination|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a divination spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can sense magical auras (as if you had cast detect magic). The range of your detection is equal to 5 feet per level of the highest-level divination spell you have available to cast. Activating or concentrating on this ability requires a standard action. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting divination spells.
Master of Undeath					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																																										PRESKILL:1,Knowledge (Religion)=5																																							DESC:You can control an undead creature that you create... for a time.																																																										MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:When you create an undead creature, you can decide that it doesn't count against your normal limit of controlled undead creatures. In this case, you still control it, but only for a number of days equal to your caster level. When that duration ends, the undead immediately becomes hostile to you (though you can establish control over it by other means). You can only have one creature controlled by this feat at a time.
Melodic Casting					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Bardic Music																																															PRESKILL:2,Perform=4,Spellcraft=4																																							DESC:You weave your music and magic together into a single perfect voice.																																																									MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.44																			BENEFIT:Whenever a Concentration check would be required, you can make a Perform check instead. In addition, you can cast spells and activate magic items by command word or spell while using bardic music. Bardic music abilities that require concentration still take a standard action to perform.
Metamagic School Focus				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus																																																																										DESC:You are unusually skilled at modifying the effects of a particular school of magic.																																																					STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SCHOOLS|FEAT=Spell Focus																																																																SOURCEPAGE:p.45																			BENEFIT:You may prepare 3 spells from your school per day with metamagic feats applied at 1 level lower than they normally would be.  You may take this feat multiple times, but for a new school each time.
Metamagic Spell Trigger				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Metamagic																													PRESKILL:1,Use Magic Device=15,Spellcraft=15																																					DESC:You can apply metamagic feats you know to spell effects from magic items you activate with a spell trigger.																																																			MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.45																			BENEFIT:You can apply any one metamagic feat you know to a spell generated by a spell trigger item (such as a wand or staff) that you activate. You expend one extra charge for each change in spell level from the feat. If the metamagic feat's level adjustment would shift the spell's level above 9th, you can't use it. If sufficient charges aren't available to activate it, nothing happens.
Metamagic Vigor					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical																									PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Metamagic																																																																									DESC:The energy you pour into increasing the power of your spells feeds back upon itself in an ever-increasing cycle.																																																		MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.45																			BENEFIT:You gain 2 maneuvers. Metamagic Intensity - If you cast spells affected by the same metamagic feat in 2 consecutive rounds, you gain a +1 bonus to caster level for the 2nd spell.  Metamagic Versatility - If you cast spells affected by two different metamagic feats in consecutive rounds, you gain a +1 bonus to the second spells save DC.  You cannot gain both benefits of this feat at the same time.
Minor Shapeshift					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=4,SPELLCASTER.Divine=4																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 4th-level spells.																		DESC:Your mastery of shapeshifting magic allows you to reshape your flesh in small but significant ways.																																																																											BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SUBSCHOOL.Polymorph|1|TYPE=Competence																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.45																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a polymorph spell of 4th level or higher available to cast, you can spend a swift action to grant yourself one of the following benefits: Might: +2 bonus on melee damage rolls. Mobility: +2 competence bonus on Balance, Climb, Jump, and Swim checks. Savagery: Primary claw attack dealing ld6 points of damage (assuming Medium size). Speed: +5-foot enhancement bonus to any one movement mode you already possess. Vigor: Temporary hit points equal to your HD. The chosen benefit lasts for a number of rounds equal to the level of the highest-level polymorph spell you have available to cast. If you activate this feat a second time while a previous benefit is still in effect, the first benefit ends immediately. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting polymorph spells. See page 91 for details on the new polymorph subschool of spells.
Mystic Backlash					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=5,SPELLCASTER.Divine=5																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 5th-level spells.																		DESC:With a touch, your magic corrupts the spells of your enemy.																																																																																		BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL.Abjuration|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.45																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an abjuration spell of 5th level or higher available to cast, you can make another creature's spellcasting harmful to itself. Use of this feat requires a melee touch attack that does not provoke attacks of opportunity. As a standard action, with a successful touch you can infuse another creature with baneful magic for a number of rounds equal to the level of the highest-level abjuration spell you have available. A successful Will save reduces this duration to 1 round. For the duration of the effect, each time the target completes the casting of a spell, it takes damage equal to the level of the abjuration spell that determined the effect's duration. Since the spell's casting has already been completed, this doesn't count as damage dealt during casting. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting abjuration spells.
Piercing Evocation				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																						PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Evocation)],[PRECLASS:1,Evoker=1]																																																					DESC:Your evocation spells ignore an amount of energy resistance.																																																											MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.46																			BENEFIT:When you cast an evocation spell that deals energy damage, you can choose for 10 points of energy damage dealt by the spell to be untyped damage to which energy resistance does not apply.
Ranged Recall					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																									PREABILITY:2,CATEGORY=FEAT,Point Blank Shot,Weapon Focus (Ranged Spell)																								PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=4																																									DESC:Your magical ranged attacks rarely miss.																																																														MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.46																			BENEFIT:When you miss with a spell or spell-like ability ranged attack against a target within 30 feet, you can spend a swift action to reroll with a -5 penalty. You may do this 3 times per day.
Rapid Metamagic					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																																										PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=12				PRESPELLCAST:MEMORIZE=N																																	DESC:You possess an uncanny mastery of magic, enabling you to modify spells on the fly much faster than others can.																																																		MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.46																			BENEFIT:When you apply a metamagic feat to a spontaneously cast spell, the spell takes only its normal casting time.
Residual Magic					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Tactical																									PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,TYPE=Metamagic																													PRESKILL:1,Spellcraft=12																																								DESC:You can use the lingering energy from a spell you cast to boost the effect of a later spell.																																																					MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.46																			BENEFIT:You gain 2 maneuvers. Enduring Potency - If you cast a spell normally, then cast the same spell from a scroll or wand in the next round, you can treat the second casting with your normal Caster Level &amp; DC.  Lingering Metamagic - If you cast a spell affected by one or more metamagic feats, and then cast the same spell in round 2 without them, you can apply any one of the metamagic feats applied to the first spell without any penalty.
Retributive Spell					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Metamagic																																																																																																						DESC:You can keep a spell in reserve to use when a foe causes you harm.																																																										MULT:NO																			ADDSPELLLEVEL:1																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.47																			BENEFIT:When you cast a spell modified by this metamagic feat, the spell has no immediate effect. Any time you are dealt damage in the next 24 hours (or when you next prepare spells), you can choose to cast the spell on that attacker as an immediate action. Once activated, it disappears. You can apply this feat only to spells with a Target creature. It will only affect the creature that attacked you, even if it would normally affect multiple targets. You may only have 1 spell prepared with this feat active at a time.
Shadow Veil						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 2nd-level spells.																		DESC:You draw wisps of darkness across your enemy's eyes, obscuring the world around him.																																																																														BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Darkness|1|TYPE=Competence																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.47																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a darkness spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can obscure the vision of a subject within 30 feet as a standard action. If the subject fails a Will save, it treats all other creatures and objects as though they had concealment and takes a -5 penalty on Spot checks for 1 round. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting darkness spells.
Sickening Grasp					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:You wreak havoc with the inner organs of a target, causing it to grow ill.																																																																															BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL.Necromancy|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.47																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a necromancy spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, any living creature you hit with a melee touch attack becomes sickened for a number of rounds equal to the level of the highest-level necromancy spell you have available to cast. The subject can reduce this duration to 1 round with a successful Fortitude save. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting necromancy spells.
Somatic Weaponry					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General																																																										PRESKILL:2,Concentration=5,Spellcraft=5																																						DESC:You are adept at performing somatic spell components while your hands are occupied.																																																							MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.47																			BENEFIT:When wiedling a weapon in one or both hands, you can use that item to trace the somatic component of a spell. This allows you to cast spells while still holding your weapon, a torch, etc... This does not allow you to cast while grappling. Normally, you would need at least 1 hand free to cast spells.
Storm Bolt						CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:The electrical energy contained within your magic rages inside you, begging to be released.																																																																												BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Electricity|1|TYPE=Competence																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.47																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an electricity spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can fire a 20-foot line of electricity as a standard action. This bolt deals ld6 points of electricity damage per level of the highest-level electricity spell you have available to cast. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting electricity spells.
Summon Elemental					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=4,SPELLCASTER.Divine=4																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 4th-level spells.																		DESC:You can channel the summoning power you hold to briefly bring forth an elemental servant.																																																																													BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SPELL.Summon Monster I|1|TYPE=Competence	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SPELL.Summon Nature's Ally I|1|TYPE=Competence																												SOURCEPAGE:p.47																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a summoning spell of 4th level or higher available to cast, you can summon a Small elemental (air, earth, fire, or water; your choice) within a range of 30 feet. The elemental acts as if summoned by a summon monster spell (PH 285). The duration of the summoning is equal to 1 round per level of the highest-level conjuration (summoning) spell you have available to cast. You can have only one summoned elemental from this feat at a time; if you use the ability a second time, the first elemental disappears. Also, you must remain close to the elemental you summon. If at the end of your turn you are more than 30 feet from the elemental, it disappears. If you have a conjuration (summoning) spell of 6th level or higher available to cast, you can summon a Medium elemental instead. If you have a conjuration (summoning) spell of 8th | level or higher available to cast, you can summon a Large elemental instead. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting conjuration (summoning) I spells.
Sunlight Eyes					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 2nd-level spells.																		DESC:The bright magic within you allows you to see through the | darkest shadow.																																																																															BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Light|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.48																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a light spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can take a swift action to grant yourself the ability to see normally in any conditions of illumination (shadowy illumination, darkness, and magical shadow or darkness). The range of this vision is 10 feet per level of the highest-level light spell you have available to cast, and the effect lasts for 1 round. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting light spells.
Touch of Distraction				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:Your touch briefly clouds the mind of a foe, impeding its efforts.																																																																																	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|SCHOOL.Enchantment|1|TYPE=Competence																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.48																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an enchantment spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can cloud the mind of a creature within 30 feet as a standard action. The target takes a -2 penalty on its next single attack roll or Reflex saving throw. If the target makes no attacks or Reflex saves within a number of rounds equal to the level of the highest-level enchantment spell you have available to cast, the effect ends. Multiple uses of this feat don't stack. This is an enchantment (compulsion), mind-affecting effect. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting enchantment spells.
Toughening Transmutation			CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Transmutation)],[PRECLASS:1,Transmuter=1]																																																				DESC:Casting a spell briefly transforms your skin or that of any ally into sterner stuff.																																																							MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.48																			BENEFIT:Whenever you cast a transmutation spell, you can choose to grant yourself or the targeted creature damage reduction 5/magic.  If they already have damage reduction, this improves it. The effect lasts for 1 round.
Unsettling Enchantment				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General.Wizard																																					PREMULT:1,[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Spell Focus (Enchantment)],[PRECLASS:1,Enchanter=1]																																																				DESC:You enchantment spells cloud the minds of even those who would otherwise resist the effects.																																																					MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.48																			BENEFIT:Any foe required to save against an enchantment spell you cast takes a -2 penalty on attack rolls and to AC for 1 round, regardless of the save result. This is a mind-affecting effect.
Vengeful Spirit					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:General		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,TYPE.Watchful Spirit																																																																																											DESC:Your watchful spirit takes revenge on foes that have harmed you.																																																										MULT:NO																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.48																			BENEFIT:If you use an initiative reroll from your watchful spirit class ability, the first creature to deal damage to you in the encounter takes half the damage it dealt to you. This damage is untyped, so DR and resistances and immunities do not apply. You also gain an extra use of watchful spirit each day.
Wind-Guided Arrows				CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=3,SPELLCASTER.Divine=3																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 3rd-level spells.																		DESC:Your mastery of the wind allows you to alter the flight of a ranged weapon.																																																																															BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Air|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.																			BENEFIT:As long as you have an air spell of 3rd level or higher available to cast, you can spend an immediate action to alter slightly the course of an arrow, crossbow bolt, spear, or other ranged weapon already in flight. You can't change the weapon's target, but you can apply a +2 bonus or -2 penalty on its attack roll. You and the target can be no farther apart than 10 feet per level of the highest-level air spell you have available, since the guidance occurs at the end of the weapon's flight. This feat works only on thrown or projectile weapons; it can't affect spells, powers, energy attacks, or the like. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting air spells.
Winter's Blast					CATEGORY:FEAT	TYPE:Reserve																PRECLASS:1,SPELLCASTER.Arcane=2,SPELLCASTER.Divine=2																																																			PRETEXT:Prerequisite: Ability to cast 2nd-level spells.																		DESC:The frozen magic within you can burst forth in a hail of frost.																																																																																	BONUS:CASTERLEVEL|DESCRIPTOR.Cold|1|TYPE=Competence																																								SOURCEPAGE:p.																			BENEFIT:As long as you have a cold spell of 2nd level or higher available to cast, you can create a 15-foot cone-shaped burst of cold. This cone deals ld4 points of cold damage per level of the highest-level cold spell you have available to cast. A successful Reflex save halves the damage. As a secondary benefit, you gain a +1 competence bonus to your caster level when casting cold spells.
